lead_paragraph: PASADENA, Calif. - The Ohio State sophomore quarterback Terrelle Pryor was nonchalant when asked about his performance Friday that earned him most valuable offensive player of the game honors in eighth-ranked Ohio State's 26-17 Rose Bowl victory against No. 7 Oregon.
snippet: The Buckeyes opened up in their Rose Bowl victory against Oregon, but their coach was noncommital about whether this marked a permanent change in philosophy.

headline.main: A Sign of Things to Come at Ohio State?
